The paper proposes a method for learning the architecture of a meta-network, which is a deep neural network that can be shared across multiple tasks. This involves using Bayesian inference and variational inference techniques. The paper also demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method on few-shot learning problems. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
